<!-- 
===================
TASK:   mean
AUTHOR: Owen Feehan
===================

===========
DESCRIPTION
===========

Calculates an image where each pixel contains the mean of that pixel-value across many images AFTER
resizing each-image to fixed dimensionality.

This task is like mean.xml but can gracefully handle differently-sized imaged as inputs.

======
INPUTS
======

Grayscale or RGB images, all must be the same size.

=======
OUTPUTS
=======

An image for each channel (resized to 1024x768), containing the mean of that channel across all images

-->
<config>
<bean config-class="org.anchoranalysis.plugin.image.task.bean.grouped.raster.GroupedMeanChnlTask">
	<resizeTo width="1024" height="768" config-class="org.anchoranalysis.image.bean.size.SizeXY"/>
</bean>
</config>